    "name": "StableCoin-ComplianceDrift-30d-iter5",
    "description": "APPROACH 3 iter5 — COMPLIANCE DRIFT MODEL (6.6): GENIUS/MiCA regulatory monitoring.\n\nMonitors 4 compliance metrics aligned to iter5 portfolio and thresholds:\n  Metric            | Weight | Threshold       | Regulatory Source\n  Backing ratio     | 40%    | >= 1.0 (100%)   | STABLE Act / GENIUS Act / MiCA EMT\n  WAM (days)        | 30%    | <= 93 days      | GENIUS Act\n  HQLA quality      | 20%    | >= 70 (not 100) | GENIUS Act (iter5 = L1+L2A+L2B portfolio)\n  Attestation age   | 10%    | <= 30 days      | All frameworks\n\nPortfolio WAM calculation (iter5, day 1):\n  tbill-4wk-001:  $10k * 18d remaining = 180,000\n  tbill-13wk-001: $32k * 49d remaining = 1,568,000\n  tbill-26wk-001: $26k * 104d remaining = 2,704,000\n  commpaper:       $6k * 43d remaining = 258,000\n  defi-yield-001:  $4k * 90d remaining = 360,000\n  WEIGHTED SUM = 5,070,000 / $78k non-cash = 65.0 days WAM (well under 93d)\n\n30-DAY LIFECYCLE:\n  Days 1-10:   Fully compliant — backing 101%, WAM 65d, quality 96, attest fresh\n  Day 11:      Halt — backing still 101% but EW fires (this is NOT a compliance breach)\n               WAM creeps up as short-tenor assets mature without replacement\n  Days 11-18:  HALT PERIOD — WAM drifts: 65d -> 82d (4wk tbill maturing improves it)\n               Attestation age creeps toward 30d limit\n  Day 18:      tbill-4wk matures, cash increases, WAM resets lower\n               Attestation issued (forced by regulatory surveillance)\n  Days 19-30:  Recovery — all metrics green, de-escalation\n\nKEY CHANGE vs stablecoin-1:\n  hqlaMinScore=70 (not 100) — iter5 has L2A/L2B instruments\n  backingThreshold=1.00 (unchanged)\n  wamMaxDays=93 (GENIUS Act — unchanged)\n  HQLA score reflects weighted quality including defi (60) and commpaper (85)\n  Compliance composite: backing (40%) dominates — stays green throughout\n\nOpen Postman Console (Ctrl+Alt+C) before running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
